               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18290115-251-person1914">
                  GEORGE 
                  DOWNIE
               <interp inst="t18290115-251-person1914" type="surname" value="DOWNIE"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18290115-251-person1914" type="given" value="GEORGE"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18290115-251-person1914" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am a <rs id="t18290115-251-viclabel1349" type="occupation">sailor</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18290115-251-victim1913 t18290115-251-viclabel1349"></join>, and live with Mr. Briant. On the 8th of January I lost these clothes from a chest by my bedside; I put them there at night, and in the morning, when I awoke, they were all gone - I never saw the prisoner; I was asleep before he came in, and when he went out.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18290115-251-person1915">
                  GEORGE 
                  BRIANT
               <interp inst="t18290115-251-person1915" type="surname" value="BRIANT"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18290115-251-person1915" type="given" value="GEORGE"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18290115-251-person1915" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I keep the <placeName id="t18290115-251-crimeloc1350">Boy and Helmet public-house, in East Smithfield</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18290115-251-crimeloc1350" type="placeName" value="Boy and Helmet public-house, in East Smithfield"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18290115-251-crimeloc1350" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18290115-251-off1347 t18290115-251-crimeloc1350"></join>; Downie lodged with me for about three weeks - on the 8th he went to bed, and the watchman brought the prisoner in quite late, and asked if I could give him a lodging; I led him up to bed - he asked what there was to pay; I said, "You are a poor man, 6d."I went into Downie's room to get a candle: told him to put it out, and bid him good night; the next morning he got up early, knocked at my door, and asked me to let him out - I got up in the dark and let him out: about seven o'clock the prosecutor came down, and said he had lost his clothes - the prisoner was afterwards found on boards a ship, but none of the property on him; no other persons slept in the house.</p>
               <p>Prisoner. I went into the room you shewed me; I put on my own clothes in the morning - I had no bundle or any thing with me. Witness. I let him out with the key, which I always take with me; I did not see him with any bundle, or that he looked more bulky than the night before.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18290115-251-person1916">
                  ROBERT 
                  HENRY BURGESS
               <interp inst="t18290115-251-person1916" type="surname" value="HENRY BURGESS"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18290115-251-person1916" type="given" value="ROBERT"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18290115-251-person1916" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I took the prisoner. I have two old shirts and a pair of old trousers, which were found in the room which the prisoner slept in that night - a key and a handkerchief were found in the prisoner's bed, which had been in the prosecutor's jacket pocket.</p>
               <p>Prisoner's Defence. He took me on board a ship, just as I was coming on board; I never saw these things in my life, which are said to have been found in my bed.</p>
               <p>GEORGE BRIANT. No one else slept in the house that night; they might possibly have been there before.</p>
               <p>
                  <rs id="t18290115-251-verdict1351" type="verdictDescription">
                     <interp inst="t18290115-251-verdict1351" type="verdictCategory" value="guilty"></interp>
               GUILTY
            </rs>. Aged 38.</p>
